Yes, I made some assumptions that didn't work, but in the end they all got figured out.

@el

The "and" simply tells us that there are two films to consider, and doesn't imply that the answer is going to be singular or plural. When given two of something to consider, it makes me  want to try to find something that either connects them or that they have in common. In this case, it was find a general category that fits both films in each clue.

That common connection is what the constructor wants us to come up with, so the plurality of the clue doesn't affect the answer at all. And in my opinion, listing only one movie in each clue would have made it more difficult to figure out what kind of an answer was required.

