@john ezra "Have any of you ever used agar as a thickener in your culinary endeavors?"

Indeed I have--"Vegan Cononut-lime Panna Cotta" is a go-to recipe for me, for the holier-than-thou set.

Curiously, agar and gelatin, although both thickeners, need to be handle not only differently, but almost oppositely: gelatin is added at the very end, and can't be overheated lest it destroy the thickening properties. Agar, OTOH, is added at the very beginning, and needs to come to a full rolling boil for a minute or two to activate. Also, the "mouth-feel" is very different--agar lacks the "jiggliness" of gelatin.

